Sentencas: Cobalt-free provskite oxides Bi0.5Sr0.5Fe1-xNbxO3-delta (BSFNx, x = 0.05, 0.10 and 0.15) were prepared and evaluated as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: A novel family of Nb-doped Bi0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ perovskite as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In particular, the effects of Nb substitution on phase evolution, thermal expansion behavior and electrochemical performance were systematically investigated.
Titulo: A novel family of Nb-doped Bi0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ perovskite as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of BSFNx decreases from 13.3 x 10(-6) K-1 at x = 0.05 to 12.6 X 10(-6) K-1 at x = 0.15 within a temperature range of 50800 degrees C. Among the BSFNx materials, Bi0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-delta (BSFN0.10) oxide shows the best electrochemical performance.
Titulo: A novel family of Nb-doped Bi0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ perovskite as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistances (R-p) of BSFN0.10 cathode on CGO electrolyte are 0.038, 0.075 and 0.156 Omega cm(2) at 700, 650 and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: A novel family of Nb-doped Bi0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ perovskite as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Meanwhile the maximum power densities of the anode-supported single cells are 1.28, 1.54 and 1.34 W cm(-2) at 700 degrees C for BSFNx cathodes with x = 0.05, 0.10, and 0.15, respectively.
Titulo: A novel family of Nb-doped Bi0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ perovskite as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, the relationship study of oxygen partial pressure dependence on R-p indicates that the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) rate-limiting step is the oxygen adsorption-dissociation on the electrode surface.
Titulo: A novel family of Nb-doped Bi0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ perovskite as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The desirable electrochemical performance demonstrates that BSFNx oxides are potential cathode materials for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: A novel family of Nb-doped Bi0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ perovskite as cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
